<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Recipex</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <div class="bg-blur"></div>
  <%-include("../partials/navbar") %>

  <main class="container">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-left">
        <div class="badge">Recipex</div><!--Name of app-->
        <h1>Plan meals faster.<br/>Eat better on a student schedule.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          MealMajor helps you organize recipes, build a weekly meal plan, and keep track of groceries —
          without the chaos.
        </p>

        <div class="hero-ctas">
          <a class="btn btn-lg" href="/register">Get started</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg" href="/login">I already have an account</a>
        </div>

        <div class="mini-stats">
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="stat-top">⏱️</div>
            <div class="stat-title">Quick planning</div>
            <div class="muted">Weekly grid view</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="stat-top">🥗</div>
            <div class="stat-title">Diet-aware</div>
            <div class="muted">Prefs + allergies</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <div class="stat-top">💸</div>
            <div class="stat-title">Budget-friendly</div>
            <div class="muted">Track cost later</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-right">
        <div class="preview-card">
          <div class="preview-head">
            <div>
              <div class="preview-title">This Week</div>
              <div class="muted">Prototype preview we will change it after</div>
            </div>
            <span class="chip">Planner</span>
          </div>

          <div class="week-grid">
            <div class="cell head">Mon</div><div class="cell head">Tue</div><div class="cell head">Wed</div>
            <div class="cell head">Thu</div><div class="cell head">Fri</div><div class="cell head">Sat</div><div class="cell head">Sun</div>

            <div class="cell">Oats</div><div class="cell">Egg wrap</div><div class="cell">Smoothie</div>
            <div class="cell">Yogurt</div><div class="cell">Porridge</div><div class="cell">Toast</div><div class="cell">Pancakes</div>

            <div class="cell">Chicken bowl</div><div class="cell">Pasta</div><div class="cell">Salad</div>
            <div class="cell">Rice + tuna</div><div class="cell">Stir-fry</div><div class="cell">Wrap</div><div class="cell">Soup</div>
          </div>

          <div class="preview-foot muted">
            Tip: later we’ll filter recipes using your allergies.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="features" class="section">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2>Built for Sprint 1 — ready for future sprints</h2>
        <p class="muted">Clean UI foundation you can extend into recipes + planner features.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card-grid">
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="icon">🔐</div>
          <h3>Login & Register</h3>
          <p class="muted">Simple, clean authentication pages with a modern layout.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="icon">👤</div>
          <h3>Profile basics</h3>
          <p class="muted">Diet preferences and allergies can plug in later.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
          <div class="icon">📅</div>
          <h3>Weekly planner</h3>
          <p class="muted">The UI already hints at a weekly grid experience.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="how" class="section split">
      <div class="split-card">
        <h2>How it works</h2>
        <ol class="steps">
          <li><span class="num">1</span> Create an account</li>
          <li><span class="num">2</span> Add your preferences</li>
          <li><span class="num">3</span> Plan your week</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <div class="split-card">
        <h2>Why students like it</h2>
        <ul class="bullets">
          <li>Less time thinking “what do I eat?”</li>
          <li>More consistent healthy meals</li>
          <li>Easy to extend with recipes + grocery tracking</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="faq" class="section">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2>FAQ</h2>
        <p class="muted">Just UI for now — backend comes next.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq">
        <details>
          <summary>Is this connected to a database?</summary>
          <p class="muted">Not yet. This is the Sprint 1 front-end. We’ll wire the backend after.</p>
        </details>
        <details>
          <summary>Can we demo login/register?</summary>
          <p class="muted">Yes — once we connect the POST routes and sessions, these pages are ready.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <%- include("../partials/footer") %>
</body>
</html>